Patch Set 11: Code-Review-1

(19 comments)

I just looked through the proposed code and did not test it at all.

The general comments:
- (tests) Compared to the number of new lines, test coverage is not good enough. More test coverage looks required.
- (style) There are many blank lines inside a import group. In the OpenStack coding guideline, we don't use blank lines inside a import group.
- (style) I see many old copyrights. I guess they are kept when borrowing codes but it depends on how many codes are borrowed. I see less original codes in some files. It looks better to recheck appropriate copyright notices are included. (OpenStack development guideline does not require the copyright notice and it totally depends on your company requirement. if your company does not, you don't need to add the copyright notice and you can only have the licence notice.)

Patch Set 11:

Thank you for your input. I will be on vacation until July 26 and will continue working on the issues and add more tests.

Patch Set 5:

Do you intend to create a job in neutron that exercises this? Would be good to see that this actually works.

Patch Set 5:

I created https://review.opendev.org/760668 to test this out (neutron jobs that set TUNNEL_IP_VERSION=6).  If it works then maybe this type of setting belongs in the base tempest job, or... ?

Patch Set 5:

So the neutron-tempest-ipv6-only-tunnel job I added in a dependent commit definitely used an IPv6 endpoint:

OVS.local_ip = 2001:4800:7818:104:be76:4eff:fe04:69cb

I am curious what the multinode job would do since I did noticed the MTU in the OVS agent was still 1450, so might require a change like https://review.opendev.org/#/c/343041/ in order for it to account for the IPv6 overhead.

So in short this patch did work.

Abandoned

Neutron patch was abandoned, feel free to restore both if you want to continue with this
